commentary: Richardson to Kohli, OUT and Rohit is run-out! Steven Smith makes the run-out with a sensational dive. A short delivery outside off, Kohli guides the ball down to backward point, where Smith dives away to his left to stop the ball. He then has a throw at the batsman's end, where Rohit and Kohli are both vying to make the crease. Head is backing up at midwicket, picks up, and throws the ball back to the bowler, who takes off the bails. Unfortunate for Rohit, Kohli was run-out here when Rohit hit that double-hundred in 2013. That's how it goes

commentary: Cummins to Patel, 1 run length ball slanting across towards off stump. Pushes at it uncertainly, his feet aren't quite moving yet, and gets an outside edge down to third man
text: length ball slanting across towards off stump. Pushes at it uncertainly, his feet aren't quite moving yet, and gets an outside edge down to third man

commentary: Cummins to Dhoni, FOUR runs back of a length, angling down leg, and Dhoni tucks it away fine, too fine for the man at fine leg to stop. Don't know if Cummins was a little put off by Dhoni's initial movement across the stumps
text: back of a length, angling down leg, and Dhoni tucks it away fine, too fine for the man at fine leg to stop. Don't know if Cummins was a little put off by Dhoni's initial movement across the stumps

commentary: Cummins to Dhoni, no run down the track and he has an almighty heave across this short ball. Inside-edges past leg stump, and Wade throws himself to his left to stop it
text: down the track and he has an almighty heave across this short ball. Inside-edges past leg stump, and Wade throws himself to his left to stop it

commentary: Cummins to Dhoni, no run short, rising ball. Too close to off stump to cut, and he's off his feet and he inside-edges down into the ground, not far from off stump
text: short, rising ball. Too close to off stump to cut, and he's off his feet and he inside-edges down into the ground, not far from off stump

commentary: Cummins to Dhoni, 1 run again a big step across his stumps. Cummins digs it in, just back of a length, angling into the body, and Dhoni swivels to pull to long leg
text: again a big step across his stumps. Cummins digs it in, just back of a length, angling into the body, and Dhoni swivels to pull to long leg

commentary: Richardson to Dhoni, no run shortish, too close to off stump to get the kind of power he wants with the cut. Straight to backward point
text: shortish, too close to off stump to get the kind of power he wants with the cut. Straight to backward point

commentary: Richardson to Dhoni, no run slower ball wide of off stump, flat-batted hard but straight to extra-cover
text: slower ball wide of off stump, flat-batted hard but straight to extra-cover

commentary: Richardson to Dhoni, no run slower ball, fullish outside off. Another huge slog from Dhoni, loses his shape, and nearly inside-edges into his off stump. Wade dives left to make sure it doesn't run away behind him
text: slower ball, fullish outside off. Another huge slog from Dhoni, loses his shape, and nearly inside-edges into his off stump. Wade dives left to make sure it doesn't run away behind him

commentary: Richardson to Dhoni, SIX runs short outside off, and Dhoni's flat-batted it for six! Finally gets some leverage, some width, and he just slaps it away over the covers
text: short outside off, and Dhoni's flat-batted it for six! Finally gets some leverage, some width, and he just slaps it away over the covers

commentary: Richardson to Dhoni, OUT bowled him! He's really not got to grips with Richardson's slower one, and he's dragged this on. Was on the cards, given how much he was hitting across these balls. Back of a length, closer to off stump this time. Goes for the big swipe over the leg side, only manages an inside-edge onto his stumps

commentary: Richardson to Mohammed Shami, no run slower short ball, angling down leg. Not the greatest of balls to bowl with fine leg inside the circle, but Shami only manages to swat it straight to that fielder

commentary: Cummins to Patel, 1 run length ball on middle and off, only manages to push towards extra cover and pick up one

commentary: Cummins to Patel, 2 runs shortish on leg stump, tucked away towards deep square leg

commentary: Cummins to Patel, 1 run back of a length on leg stump. Looks to whip it against the angle, gets a leading edge that loops up and drops into no-man's land in front of deep square leg running in
